cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper discusses a novel approach for large-scale multi-label learning using distributional semantics, which is a subfield of natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves matrix factorization and regression models, which are common in machine learning and data mining, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions incorporating label-label correlations, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper includes experiments on benchmark datasets involving image classification, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
